tweet: Listening to @twoscooters talk about how harassment is important. And how we are going to help you through it.

label: none
tweet: "I'm bringing it up for one reason. GamerGate has brought harassment into the limelight, but rest assured, it's always there."

label: none
tweet: This is a problem that affects everyone, but we have seen far more harassment targeting women.

label: none
tweet: It is fitting that we are now seeing these strong women speaking out and trying to fix problems that others are uncertain of how to tackle.

label: none
tweet: Oh gosh she mentioned me and #ggautoblocker in her talk and now I am blushing and trying not to sniffle.

label: none
tweet: In this ongoing tragedy, we found our voices & each other. We have learned to work together, and to support & encourage these amazing women.

label: none
tweet: I can't even find the words to describe how much I value the work of all the people I've met during this time. How much I love all of them.

label: none
tweet: We talk about GamerGate a lot. But the truth is, GamerGate isn't the real battle. It's a symptom of a larger problem.

label: none
tweet: Online harassment is something most people have faced at some point, regardless of their views on ethics in games journalism.

label: none
tweet: It's a really tough problem, because it's a BIG problem. It is far reaching. It has many different forms.

label: none
tweet: The scope of the problem can discourage people from trying to fight it. Often this leads to thinking, "what can I do? I'm just one person."

label: none
tweet: You aren't just one person. There are many of us, and we all have voices. But more than that, we have resources, experience, and passion.

label: none
tweet: You aren't alone in this. You're never alone in this.

label: none
tweet: We have seen so many fantastic things happen out of this tragedy. First, we have @femfreq. Amazing advocacy. A voice that is far reaching.

label: none
tweet: We have @crashoverridenw, an invaluable resource that provides emotional support for targets of harassment.

label: none
tweet: Both of these organizations have been created to address different aspects of very real problems that affect all of us.
